# Core Conventions for gstack-framework

## Skill conventions
- Skills are standalone markdown files in `skills/{name}/SKILL.md`
- Every skill has YAML frontmatter with: name, description (multi-line with triggers), allowed-tools
- Every skill uses phase-based workflow: Context -> Analysis -> Action -> Verification -> Report
- Every skill has a verification step requiring evidence (not claims)
- Every skill has stop conditions (both "stop for" and "never stop for")
- Every skill has voice directive banning AI slop vocabulary
- Every skill has Completion Status Protocol (DONE, BLOCKED, NEEDS_CONTEXT)

## Template conventions
- Templates live in `templates/` with `.tmpl` extension
- All placeholders use `{{PLACEHOLDER}}` syntax (double curly braces, ALL_CAPS)
- Placeholder names are part of the public API. Renaming breaks the apply skill.
- When adding a new placeholder, update `skills/apply/SKILL.md` in the same commit

## Checklist conventions
- Checklists live in `checklists/` as markdown files
- Each checkbox item has a point value in brackets: `- [ ] [2] Description`
- Point values must sum correctly within each category
- Pass thresholds: 70/100 ship-ready, 85/100 production-grade, 95/100 reference-quality

## Non-destructive principle
- Never overwrite existing files without user confirmation
- Show diffs before applying changes
- The framework adds alongside, never replaces silently

## Backward compatibility
- Existing skill names and interfaces are stable
- Template placeholder names are stable
- Checklist point totals are stable
- Adding new skills, templates, or checklists is always safe
- Modifying existing interfaces requires a deprecation path

## File naming
- Skills: kebab-case directory name matching the `name` field in frontmatter
- Templates: PascalCase or UPPER-CASE filename with `.tmpl` extension
- Checklists: kebab-case with `.md` extension

## Quality gate
- Every SKILL.md must score 35+ on `checklists/skill-quality.md` before merge
- Every repo transformation must score 70+ on `checklists/repo-quality.md`
